helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear,

I am writing to address an issue regarding a recent full body checkup
booking for my father.

I booked a "comprehensive full body checkup test with Vitamin D and B12
package along with PPBS test" for December 8, 2025, and paid 1368 online.

Upon the technician's arrival, she informed us that due to low blood flow,
the PPBS test needed to be canceled. We agreed, and she canceled the test
from her end. I expected a partial refund since the test was removed.
Instead, the updated invoice showed an extra amount of 581 was due, which
I reluctantly paid as I could not reach any Pharmeasy associates via the
number 7022000900 despite multiple attempts. The technician assured me I
would receive a refund.

However, when I finally connected with customer care, I was informed that
the removal of the PPBS test resulted in the removal of a discount coupon,
leading to the extra charge. I find this explanation confusing, as the
current price for the "comprehensive full body checkup test with Vitamin D
and B12 package" on your app is 1399, yet I was charged a total of 1949
(1368 + 581). If any test was removed by your technician, it is a fault
on your end. There were alternate coupons also available which should have
been auto-applied. This total is significantly higher and even exceeds the
local market price of approximately 1500 for the same tests.

I request a thorough review of this billing discrepancy and an immediate
refund of the extra amount charged. As a regular customer who has
previously ordered several test packages and medicines from Pharmeasy, this
instance is concerning. Failure to provide a proper resolution will
unfortunately lead me to discontinue ordering services from Pharmeasy in
the future.

Kindly look into this matter urgently and process the necessary refund.


Regards,
Razaali Bana

Assistant Manager, Metadata Production

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Razaali Bana <razaali.bana@nielsen.com>
Date: Sun, Dec 7, 2025 at 6:07PM
Subject: Billing Issue
To: care@pharmeasy.in <care@pharmeasy.in>, grievance-officer@pharmeasy.in <grievance-officer@pharmeasy.in>


Dear,

I am writing to address an issue regarding a recent full body checkup booking for my father.

I booked a "comprehensive full body checkup test with Vitamin D and B12 package along with PPBS test" for December 8, 2025, and paid 1368 online.

Upon the technician's arrival, she informed us that due to low blood flow, the PPBS test needed to be canceled. We agreed, and she canceled the test from her end. I expected a partial refund since the test was removed. Instead, the updated invoice showed an extra amount of 581 was due, which I reluctantly paid as I could not reach any Pharmeasy associates via the number 7022000900 despite multiple attempts. The technician assured me I would receive a refund.

However, when I finally connected with customer care, I was informed that the removal of the PPBS test resulted in the removal of a discount coupon, leading to the extra charge.I find this explanation confusing, as the current price for the "comprehensive full body checkup test with Vitamin D and B12 package" on your app is 1399, yet I was charged a total of 1949 (1368 + 581). If any test was removed by your technician, it is a fault on your end. There were alternate coupons also available which should have been auto-applied. This total is significantly higher and even exceeds the local market price of approximately 1500 for the same tests.
I request a thorough review of this billing discrepancy and an immediate refund of the extra amount charged. As a regular customer who has previously ordered several test packages and medicines from Pharmeasy, this instance is concerning. Failure to provide a proper resolution will unfortunately lead me to discontinue ordering services from Pharmeasy in the future.

Kindly look into this matter urgently and process the necessary refund.


Regards,
Razaali Bana

notes.body: Hello Chirag,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regards to promotional notifications, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number '7203046067' from getting the promotional notifications. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual sim phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well, we will forward a request for the other number as well.     Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email id too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.     I certainly hope this helps, and appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile.     For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the Need Help section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay healthy!     Regards,  Habiba
